The most literate city in the country, with the highest percentage of residents with a college degree or higher. The bridge that connects Seattle and Medina across Lake Washington is the world’s longest floating bridge.
San Francisco was the northern core of Spanish and Mexican interest in California during the gold rush. Its physical geography includes seep slopes, giving you beautiful views of the Pacific Ocean.
The Cascades-Coast Mountains is the snowiest portion of North America, due to its many peaks and snow being the primary variation of precipitation.
Victoria was the first permanent European settlement in the North Pacific Coast and was the largest town in British Columbia for over four decades in the 19th century.

Seattle has been the largest city along the North Pacific Coast since the late nineteenth century. It is the birthplace of companies like Boeing Aircraft and Microsoft, and it was the center of the grunge rock movement in the 90's (Pearl Jam, Soundgarden, etc.)

Honolulu is by far the biggest city in Hawaii, with over 67 percent of the state's residents and 80 percent of its economy concentrated in the city. One of the negatives of the city is that it's the most expensive city in the U.S.
